	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Monday&#44; 3rd of Kislev&#40;Nov&#41;&#44; 1865</date>.</p>
				<p>Dear friend&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Only on <date>Friday</date> did I come in possession of the &#8220;Occident&#8221;&#44;<lb/> and I am very thankful to you for the quite correct printing of the arti<lb/>cle. Nevertheless&#44; I found mistakes in the printing and 2 which I note<lb/> <del>&#63;</del> on the last of this letter which are quite serious&#44; so that you will not make<lb/> the same mistakes in the <date>January</date> issue. I must again dispense with a note<lb/> or a judgment on your part &#8212; my health is quite affected. I can&#39;t work<lb/> as much anymore. Is it any wonder&#63; Sorrow&#44; worry&#44; <sic>andannoyances</sic> bend<lb/> me low&#44; me&#44; the proud man&#44; they bend downward. If it is possible&#44; I shall<lb/> send you&#44; by the <date>20th</date>&#44; more of my work with which you will not have so<lb/> much to occupy yourself.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In any event&#44; I expect that you will translate the article<lb/> completely for the <date>January</date> number. Secondly&#44; to complete the introduction<lb/> and send me the proof sheets betimes. I also want you <sic>toprint</sic> in the<lb/> <del>&#63;</del> &#8220;Occident&#8221; <sic>myarticle</sic> in the &#8220;Jewish Messenger&#8221;.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">And now a word in the open. &#8220;Open reproof is better than<lb/> love in secret&#8221;. Your article about the <del>&#63;</del>&#44; affected<lb/> me most painfully&#44; an for a double reason. For I respect and love you<lb/> sincerely. First because the matter is <sic>criticised</sic> severely&#44; secondly<lb/> because the people are right. Through such impolite means&#44; we shall<lb/> never arrive at the goal. How is it possible that in a city like <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> a board should be organized by 33 ignoramuses&#44;&#45; reverends and chazanim&#63;<lb/> Is there not the reform party correct when it pokes fun at the affair&#63;<lb/> The board in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> is fairly <del>&#63;</del> good&#44; especially with such per&#45;<lb/>sonalities&#44; but it&#44; too&#44; lacks a respectable leader. So&#44; for God&#39;s sake&#44;<lb/> you continue your old horse in relation to the reformers. One must com&#45;<lb/>pletely ignore them&#44; as if they did not exist&#44; and stride ahead with re&#45;<lb/>ligious conservative ideas&#44; conscious of the time. Thus independence<lb/> will be developed. The articles must be made worthy. Would you perhaps<lb/> like to print&#44; in the <date>January</date> number&#44; my German article&#63; If so&#44; I will<lb/> send it to you&#44; and my article will create a sensation. But I must say</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>that if you must continue my Hebrew article in the <date>January</date> issue&#44;<lb/> otherwise&#44; I must ask you to send it back to me&#44; since I want to have it<lb/> printed in <placeName>Europe</placeName> in pamphlet form.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Did you <sic>forwars</sic> my letter to <persName>Jacob Friedman</persName>&#63; I have<lb/> received no answer from him. I beg of you to remind him.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Send me 50 copies of your small catechism bound.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I call your attention to the fact that I have moved my<lb/> office to <placeName>117 Nassau Street&#44; Room 10</placeName>. Please send everything there.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">With sincere respect&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Your loyal friend&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Jonah of the house of Bondi</persName></p>
				<p>I must also ask you to print my German articles either at the end or in<lb/> an appendix. That is to your advantage&#44; too.</p>
		</body>
